<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta name="description" content="A sample blog post demonstrating the usage of anchor tags, title tags, and other HTML elements.">
    <title>My Blog Post on HTML Tags</title> <!-- Title Tag -->
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to My HTML Tag Demonstration Blog Post</h1> <!-- Heading Tag (H1) -->
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Understanding the Anchor Tag</h2> <!-- Heading Tag (H2) -->
        <p>
            The anchor tag is used to create hyperlinks in your content. Here's an example of an anchor tag:
        </p>
        <p>
            Click <a href="https://example.com" title="Visit Example Website">here</a> to visit an example website. <!-- Anchor Tag with title attribute -->
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Using Heading Tags for Structure</h2> <!-- Heading Tag (H2) -->
        <p>
            HTML offers different levels of heading tags from <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> to <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code> to organize content hierarchically. The <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> tag is typically used for the main title, while <code>&lt;h2&gt;</code> through <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code> are used for subheadings.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Embedding Images with the Image Tag</h2> <!-- Heading Tag (H2) -->
        <p>
            Here's how you can embed an image into your blog post using the <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tag:
        </p>
        <p>
            <img src="https://example.com/sample-image.jpg" alt="Sample Image" title="Sample Image Title"> <!-- Image Tag with alt and title attributes -->
        </p>
        <p>
            The <code>alt</code> attribute provides an alternative text for the image if it cannot be displayed, and the <code>title</code> attribute shows additional information when you hover over the image.
        </p>
    </section>

    <footer>
        <p>Thank you for reading! For more information, visit <a href="https://mysite.com" title="My Blog">My Blog</a>.</p> <!-- Anchor Tag -->
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
